at%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20an%20excellent%20choice%20if%20you%20prefer%20the%20same%20vest%20style%2C%20just%20without%20the%20harness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2275b27020-6f12-498a-b1c2-81ef1d651eed%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20to%20look%20for%5C%22%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20a%20dog%20winter%20coat%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECollins%20says%20to%20first%20consider%20your%20dog's%20needs%20and%20preferences%20when%20picking%20out%20a%20dog%20winter%20coat.%20Is%20your%20dog%20more%20of%20a%20fair-weather%20friend%20who%20just%20needs%20a%20simple%20coat%20for%20potty%20breaks%20and%20quick%20walks%2C%20or%20are%20they%20a%20winter-weather%20lover%20who%20needs%20an%20insulated%2C%20waterproof%20option%20for%20vigorous%20romps%20in%20the%20snow%20and%20playtime%20with%20friends%3F%20These%20answers%20will%20guide%20you%20in%20finding%20the%20best%20winter%20coat%20for%20your%20dog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20other%20tips%20from%20our%20veterinarian%20experts%20to%20help%20you%20narrow%20your%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFit%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECollins%20also%20stresses%20the%20importance%20of%20a%20good%20fit.%20Your%20dog's%20coat%20should%20be%20easy%20to%20put%20on%2C%20take%20off%2C%20and%20move%20around%20in.%20He%20adds%20that%20it%20should%20strike%20a%20balance%20between%20not%20being%20too%20loose%20and%20not%20being%20too%20tight%2C%20so%20it%20doesn't%20restrict%20movement%20or%20irritate%20the%20skin.%20Additionally%2C%20consider%20the%20overall%20length%20and%20coverage%20to%20ensure%20the%20coat%20doesn't%20get%20in%20the%20way%20of%20potty%20breaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdjustability%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECollins%20says%20winter%20coats%20that%20can%20be%20adjusted%20in%20multiple%20places%20may%20work%20best%20for%20dogs%20with%20particular%20body%20shapes%20and%20coat%20types%2C%20like%20barrel-chested%20breeds%20and%20long-haired%20dogs.%20However%2C%20he%20notes%20that%20the%20adjustment%20points%20should%20stay%20securely%20in%20place%20and%20not%20come%20easily%20undone%20under%20normal%20use.%20He%20adds%20that%20the%20adjustments%20should%20also%20be%20easy%20for%20the%20person%20putting%20on%20the%20coat%20and%20be%20well-tolerated%20by%20the%20dog.%20For%20instance%2C%20an%20adjustable%20waistband%20that's%20hard%20to%20snap%20shut%20will%20be%20difficult%20for%20guardians%20with%20mobility%20issues%2C%20while%20one%20that%20clasps%20loudly%20might%20frighten%20fearful%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterial%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20The%20type%20and%20quality%20of%20a%20coat's%20material%20affect%20how%20well%20it%20protects%20against%20cold%20temperatures%2C%20resists%20moisture%2C%20and%20blocks%20strong%20winds.%20If%20you%20live%20in%20a%20particularly%20wet%2C%20snowy%2C%20or%20windy%20climate%2C%20look%20for%20waterproof%20fabrics%20like%20nylon%20or%20polyester.%20For%20protection%20against%20the%20cold%2C%20fleece%20and%20polyester%20are%20effective%20insulators%2C%20and%20their%20soft%20texture%20is%20often%20comfortable%20for%20dogs.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcvm.ncsu.edu%2Fpeople%2Fslvaden%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Shelly%20Vaden%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20veterinarian%20and%20professor%20of%20nephrology%20and%20urology%20at%20the%20NC%20State%20University%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine%2C%20recommends%20looking%20for%20reflective%20materials%2C%20like%20piping%20and%20strips%2C%20if%20you%20walk%20your%20dog%20in%20heavy-traffic%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDesign%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWinter%20dog%20coats%20vary%20in%20design%2C%20so%20check%20if%20their%20features%20are%20compatible%20with%20you%20and%20your%20dog's%20lifestyle.%20For%20instance%2C%20if%20your%20dog%20wears%20a%20harness%2C%20a%20coat%20with%20a%20back%20cutout%20for%20a%20leash%20is%20ideal.%20Or%2C%20if%20you%20have%20an%20especially%20wiggly%20pup%20who%20struggles%20to%20sit%20still%20when%20it's%20time%20for%20a%20walk%2C%20consider%20a%20coat%20with%20a%20straightforward%20closure%20system%20instead%20of%20an%20overly%20complex%20design%20with%20multiple%20straps%2C%20clips%2C%20and%20leg%20openings.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvetmedbiosci.colostate.edu%2Fdirectory%2Fmember%2F%3Fid%3Dalison-meindl-41390%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Alison%20Meindl%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20assistant%20professor%20of%20community%20practice%20at%20Colorado%20State%20University%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine%2C%20recommends%20simpler%2C%20faster%20velcro%20straps%20for%20dogs%20who%20may%20be%20sensitive%20to%20being%20handled%20or%20dislike%20items%20being%20placed%20over%20their%20heads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECare%20instructions%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESnow%2C%20slush%2C%20and%20rain%20are%20prime%20ingredients%20for%20a%20muddy%2C%20gritty%20environment%20and%20can%20quickly%20soil%20your%20dog's%20coat%20during%20walks.%20To%20keep%20a%20coat%20clean%20and%20prevent%20bacterial%20growth%20that%20thrives%20in%20moist%20conditions%2C%20look%20for%20coats%20made%20with%20machine-washable%20materials.%20Vaden%20also%20recommends%20choosing%20a%20washable%20fabric%20that%20won't%20shrink%20since%20it's%20important%20to%20wash%20a%20coat%20regularly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228a9ae232-cff4-489d-9553-2d02d22048a8%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20we%20tested%5C%22%3EHow%20we%20tested%20the%20best%20dog%20winter%20coats%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20tan%20dog%20sits%20indoors%20on%20a%20wooden%20floor%20beside%20a%20clothing%20rack%20filled%20with%20colorful%20dog%20jackets%20hanging%20on%20wooden%20hangers.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F696fff48d3c7faef0ecc9a6e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EElizabeth%20Holbrook%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFreelance%20reporter%20and%20professional%20dog%20trainer%20Shoshi%20Parks%20originally%20wrote%20this%20guide%20based%20on%20reporting%20and%20recommendations%20from%20dog%20walkers%20across%20the%20country.%20Later%2C%20reporter%20Alex%20Rennie%20conducted%20additional%20reporting%20and%20tested%20the%20Petrageous%20Designs%20Juneau%20Coat%20with%20his%20small%20terrier%20dog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20freelance%20reporter%20Elizabeth%20Holbrook%20has%20conducted%20further%20research%2C%20testing%20new%20and%20old%20options%2C%20with%20her%2040-pound%20rescue%20mix.%20Holbrook%20also%20looped%20in%20Roo's%20friend%20Remy%2C%20a%20sheepadoodle%20of%20similar%20size%2C%20for%20extra%20insight%20into%20the%20Ruffwear%20Powder%20Hound%20Jacket.%20Additionally%2C%20deals%20editor%20Sarah%20Saril%20tested%20our%20large%20winter%20coat%20contender%20with%20her%2060-pound%20German%20shepherd.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20factors%20we%20considered%20in%20our%20testing%20to%20make%20our%20top%20picks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFit%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20first%20thing%20we%20did%20with%20each%20coat%20was%20check%20whether%20the%20size%20matched%20the%20brand's%20listed%20measurements.%20We%20also%20confirmed%20whether%20the%20brand%20was%20accurate%20about%20sizing%20up%20or%20down%20when%20dogs%20were%20between%20sizes.%20Next%2C%20we%20tried%20the%20coats%20on%20our%20dogs%20to%20see%20how%20easy%20they%20were%20to%20put%20on%2C%20take%20off%2C%20and%20adjust.%20If%20it%20was%20a%20good%20fit%2C%20our%20dogs%20wore%20the%20coat%20on%20at%20least%20two%2010-minute%20walks.%20While%20outside%2C%20we%20checked%20if%20any%20part%20of%20the%20coat%20restricted%20mobility%2C%20caused%20chasing%20or%20discomfort%2C%20or%20interfered%20with%20going%20to%20the%20bathroom.%20We%20also%20noted%20if%20there%20were%20any%20issues%20with%20the%20leash%20hole%20size%20or%20placement.%20Finally%2C%20we%20examined%20how%20well%20the%20coat's%20coverage%20shielded%20the%20back%2C%20chest%2C%20belly%2C%20neck%2C%20and%20other%20key%20areas%20from%20the%20elements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWarmth%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETo%20test%20how%20well%20the%20winter%20coats%20retained%20heat%2C%20we%20filled%20a%20silicone%20water%20bottle%20with%20water%20heated%20to%20100%20degrees%20%E2%80%94%20similar%20to%20a%20dog's%20natural%20body%20temperature.%20We%20then%20placed%20the%20water%20bottle%20outside%20in%20the%20cold%2C%20with%20temperatures%20ranging%20from%2040%20to%2045%20degrees.%20After%2030%20minutes%2C%20we%20tested%20the%20water%20with%20a%20kitchen%20thermometer%20to%20see%20how%20much%20the%20warm%20water%20had%20cooled.%20On%20average%2C%20we%20discovered%20the%20temperature%20would%20drop%2010%20to%2013%20degrees%20when%20the%20water%20bottle%20was%20exposed%20directly%20to%20the%20elements.%20This%20was%20our%20baseline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20repeated%20the%20same%20steps%20for%20each%20coat%3A%20filling%20the%20bottle%20with%20water%20heated%20to%20100%20degrees%2C%20wrapping%20the%20coat%20around%20the%20bottle%2C%20and%20leaving%20it%20outside%20for%2030%20minutes.%20We%20then%20tested%20the%20temperature%20again%20to%20see%20how%20well%20it%20retained%20the%20water's%20warmth%20in%20comparison%20to%20our%20baseline%20and%20the%20other%20coats.%20Each%20coat%20in%20our%20guide%20performed%20above%20the%20baseline%2C%20with%20temperatures%20only%20dropping%20between%203%20and%205%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDurability%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBefore%20testing%20each%20coat%2C%20we%20carefully%20examined%20it%20for%20defects%20or%20poor%20construction.%20To%20ensure%20the%20fabric%20and%20hardware%20could%20withstand%20typical%20dog%20antics%20like%20scraping%20against%20trees%20and%20bushes%2C%20we%20took%20a%20dinner%20fork%2C%20pressed%20it%20down%20forcefully%2C%20and%20scratched%20each%20coat.%20We%20also%20tugged%20on%20buckles%2C%20zippers%2C%20and%20straps%20and%20operated%20zippers%20and%20velcro%20closures%20at%20least%2020%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWaterproofing%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20For%20our%20soak%20test%2C%20we%20placed%20a%20towel%20inside%20each%20coat%20and%20let%20the%20shower%20run%20on%20it%20for%20two%20minutes.%20We%20then%20let%20the%20moisture%20sit%20on%20the%20coat%20for%20half%20an%20hour%20before%20checking%20whether%20the%20towel%20and%20the%20coat's%20interior%20remained%20dry.%20We%20also%20noted%20whether%20the%20coat%20was%20considerably%20heavier%20or%20whether%20the%20liner%20felt%20cold%20after%20being%20drenched.%20After%20conducting%20our%20cleaning%20test%2C%20we%20repeated%20this%20step%20for%20each%20coat%20to%20assess%20whether%20washing%20affected%20its%20waterproofing%20abilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECare%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20To%20determine%20how%20easy%20the%20coats%20were%20to%20clean%2C%20we%20rubbed%20them%20with%20mud%20and%20let%20them%20sit%20overnight.%20The%20next%20day%2C%20we%20wiped%20each%20muddy%20patch%20with%20a%20wet%20cloth%20to%20see%20how%20easy%20they%20were%20to%20spot%20clean.%20We%20then%20followed%20the%20label's%20washing%20instructions%2C%20noting%20if%20any%20required%20special%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22087b458b-52f2-448f-a332-055b6bdf9d13%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22FAQs%5C%22%3EDog%20winter%20coat%20FAQs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3EShould%20dogs%20wear%20coats%20in%20the%20winter%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAnytime%20you're%20feeling%20the%20cold%2C%20there's%20no%20harm%20in%20putting%20a%20coat%20on%20your%20dog%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.careers.bondvet.com%2Flife-at-bond-vet%2Fmedical-excellence%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Zay%20Satchu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20chief%20veterinary%20officer%20and%20co-founder%20of%20Bond%20Vet%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20more%20likely%20to%20let%20you%20know%20they%20are%20feeling%20toasty%20by%20panting%20than%20to%20let%20you%20know%20they%20are%20chilly%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20notes.%20Collins%20adds%20that%20a%20winter%20coat%20can%20help%20keep%20a%20dog%20dry%2C%20protected%20from%20the%20wind%2C%20and%20insulated%20to%20reduce%20heat%20loss.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20a%20coat%2C%20some%20dogs%20will%20become%20uncomfortable%20and%20can%20even%20be%20at%20risk%20for%20hypothermia%20if%20exposed%20to%20the%20cold%20for%20too%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20If%20you're%20unsure%20whether%20your%20dog%20is%20cold%2C%20look%20for%20indicators%20like%20shaking%20or%20shivering%2C%20a%20hunched%20posture%20with%20a%20tucked%20tail%2C%20reluctance%20to%20move%2C%20and%20lifting%20paws%20while%20standing%20in%20the%20same%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EAt%20what%20temperature%20does%20a%20dog%20need%20a%20coat%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20isn't%20a%20specific%20temperature%2C%20but%20I%20think%20it's%20helpful%20to%20consider%20a%20coat%20when%20the%20temperature%20drops%20below%20freezing%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Collins.%20He%20recommends%20thinking%20about%20other%20factors%20as%20well%2C%20like%20windchill%2C%20precipitation%2C%20the%20length%20of%20time%20your%20dog%20will%20be%20spending%20outside%2C%20and%20what%20activity%20they'll%20be%20doing.%20Dog-related%20variables%2C%20such%20as%20breed%2C%20size%2C%20fur%20type%2C%20and%20health%2C%20will%20also%20determine%20when%20to%20don%20your%20pup%20with%20a%20cozy%20coat.%20Additionally%2C%20if%20it's%20cold%20enough%20that%20you%20need%20to%20cover%20every%20bit%20of%20your%20exposed%20skin%20to%20feel%20somewhat%20comfortable%2C%20you%20should%20stick%20to%20bringing%20your%20dog%20outdoors%20for%20only%20quick%20potty%20breaks%20instead%20of%20longer%20walks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDo%20dog%20coats%20really%20keep%20dogs%20warm%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20a%20properly%20fitted%20coat%20made%20with%20insulated%20materials%20can%20help%20keep%20your%20dog%20warm%20by%20trapping%20in%20their%20body%20heat.%20A%20waterproof%20outer%20shell%20can%20also%20block%20cold%20water%20and%20frigid%20winds.%20However%2C%20winter%20dog%20coats%20aren't%20always%20necessary.%20Vaden%20says%20many%20dogs%20do%20not%20need%20coats%20to%20keep%20warm%2C%20and%20even%20though%20it%20may%20seem%20cold%20to%20us%2C%20their%20natural%20coats%20provide%20adequate%20protection.%20%26quot%3BSome%20breeds%20will%20actually%20develop%20a%20thicker%20coat%20in%20the%20winter%20to%20aid%20in%20protection%20from%20the%20cold%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20should%20dogs%20wear%20in%20the%20snow%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20dogs%20in%20the%20snow%20for%20an%20extended%20period%2C%20Vaden%20recommends%20waterproof%20materials%20or%20insulated%20coats%2C%20as%20well%20as%20dog%20boots%20to%20protect%20their%20paws.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-boots%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20dog%20boots%3C%2Fa%3E%20help%20keep%20your%20dog%20warm%20and%20comfortable%20by%20protecting%20their%20sensitive%20paws%20from%20snow%2C%20ice%2C%20and%20salty%20sidewalks.%20%26quot%3BBooties%20are%20similar%20to%20you%20wearing%20gloves%20during%20the%20cool%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20Satchu%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20breeds%20should%20wear%20a%20coat%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDogs%20that%20more%20commonly%20need%20coats%20include%20elderly%20dogs%2C%20dogs%20that%20are%20underweight%20or%20have%20medical%20problems%2C%20dogs%20with%20arthritis%2C%20small%2Ftoy%20breed%20dogs%2C%20and%20dogs%20with%20short%2C%20thin%2C%20or%20clipped%20coats%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Collins.%20He%20adds%20that%20dogs%20closer%20to%20the%20ground%2C%20especially%20long-haired%20ones%2C%20could%20benefit%20from%20a%20coat%20to%20keep%20their%20undersides%20protected%20from%20icy%20water%2C%20salt%2C%20and%20snow.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20double-coated%20breeds%20and%20dogs%20with%20thick%20winter%20fur%2C%20like%20Siberian%20huskies%20and%20Alaskan%20malamutes%2C%20will%20have%20less%20need%20for%20a%20winter%20coat.%20Collins%20notes%20that%20these%20dogs%20may%20even%20become%20too%20warm%20while%20wearing%20a%20coat%20in%20milder%20conditions%20or%20under%20increased%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22957d8997-1f5f-4809-8e4e-ef2b637badf6%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20to%20measure%20your%20dog%20for%20a%20coat%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20measure%20your%20dog%20for%20a%20winter%20coat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20a%20proper%20fit%2C%20gather%20your%20dog's%20measurements%20rather%20than%20eyeballing%20them.%20Then%2C%20cross-reference%20your%20measurements%20with%20the%20coat's%20sizing%20instructions%20before%20ordering.%20Here%20are%20some%20tips%20on%20how%20to%20get%20the%20sizing%20right%20for%20your%20dog's%20winter%20coat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELength%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBack%20length%20is%20the%20primary%20way%20to%20determine%20what%20size%20coat%20your%20dog%20will%20need.%20Measure%20your%20dog%20while%20they're%20standing%20in%20a%20relaxed%20position%20from%20their%20shoulder%20blades%20to%20the%20base%20of%20the%20tail.%20If%20your%20dog's%20measurements%20are%20between%20sizes%2C%20go%20with%20the%20larger%20option%2C%20unless%20the%20brand%20says%20otherwise.%20Sometimes%2C%20a%20brand%20will%20also%20suggest%20a%20specific%20size%20based%20on%20breed%20or%20weight.%20While%20this%20can%20be%20helpful%2C%20don't%20use%20it%20as%20your%20only%20guide%3B%20body%20types%20vary%20drastically%20among%20different%20dogs%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bsame%26quot%3B%20type.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChest%20girth%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Since%20most%20jackets%20can't%20be%20adjusted%20around%20the%20chest%2C%20getting%20this%20measurement%20right%20is%20crucial%2C%20especially%20for%20broad%20or%20barrel-chested%20pups.%20Measure%20the%20circumference%20of%20your%20dog's%20chest%20at%20their%20largest%20point%20right%20behind%20the%20front%20legs%20while%20they're%20standing.%20Again%2C%20go%20with%20the%20larger%20option%20if%20your%20dog's%20between%20chest%20sizes.%20If%20you%20have%20an%20active%20dog%20that%20does%20a%20lot%20of%20running%20and%20jumping%2C%20you%20may%20want%20to%20add%20another%20inch%20or%20two%20to%20ensure%20they%20can%20freely%20move%20while%20wearing%20the%20coat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENeck%20girth%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETo%20get%20the%20right%20fit%20on%20a%20winter%20coat%20with%20a%20non-adjustable%20neck%20opening%2C%20measure%20around%20the%20thickest%20part%2C%20right%20below%20where%20the%20collar%20sits.%20As%20with%20the%20other%20measurements%2C%20size%20up%20when%20in%20doubt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDrop%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Sometimes%2C%20a%20coat%20will%20offer%20a%20drop%20measurement.%20This%20indicates%20how%20low%20a%20jacket%20hangs%20on%20your%20dog's%20body%20and%20legs.%20If%20the%20coat%20is%20too%20long%2C%20it%20may%20restrict%20their%20movement.%20If%20it's%20too%20short%2C%20it%20may%20not%20provide%20adequate%20coverage.%20Ideally%2C%20the%20coat%20will%20completely%20cover%20your%20dog's%20back%20but%20extend%20less%20than%20halfway%20down%20their%20leg.%20To%20determine%20how%20a%20winter%20coat%20will%20drape%20across%20your%20dog%2C%20compare%20the%20width%20of%20the%20coat%20with%20the%20distance%20between%20your%20dog's%20tail%20tip%20and%20their%20back%20ankle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-winter-coats%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1768949555000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F697001c0a645d1188187ab1d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-winter-coats%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22We%20tested%20the%20best%20dog%20winter%20coats%20with%20small%20and%20large%20pups.%20Our%20top%20picks%20include%20waterproof%2C%20insulated%20jackets%20with%20excellent%20coverage.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Elizabeth%20Holbrook%2CShoshi%20Parks%2CSorin%20McKnight)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22